<subSubSection id="C35C652C815745563DA329ABFE87D2B9" box="[136,364,446,473]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BF936A7815745563DA329ABFE87D2B9" blockId="13.[136,1452,446,1301]" box="[136,364,446,473]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
<heading id="D0B181CB815745563DA329ABFE87D2B9" bold="true" box="[136,364,446,473]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563DA329ABFE87D2B9" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[136,364,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563DA329ABFE87D2B9" bold="true" box="[136,364,446,473]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C652C815745563DA329F7FA48D700" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF936A7815745563DA329F7FE35D1D1" blockId="13.[136,1452,446,1301]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
There are relatively a few species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563F6F29F7FD45D29C" authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1844" box="[580,686,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563F6F29F7FD45D29C" box="[580,686,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in the Tajik Gorny Badakhshan. In the latest floristic treatment for 
<collectingCountry id="F3517637815745563C0C2A13FE7ED140" box="[295,405,518,544]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B56815745563C832A13FD7FD140" author="Korovin, E. P. &amp; Pimenov, M. G. &amp; Kinzikayeva, G. K." box="[424,660,518,544]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" pagination="10 - 214" refId="ref10344" refString="Korovin, E. P., Pimenov, M. G. &amp; Kinzikayeva, G. K. (1984) Umbelliferae Moris. In: Ovchinnikov, P. N. (Ed.) Flora of the Tajik SSR, vol. 7. Academy of Sciences of USSR, Moscow &amp; Leningrad, pp. 10 - 214. [In Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1984">
Korovin 
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563F3A2A12FDA6D140" box="[529,589,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">et al.</emphasis>
1984
</bibRefCitation>
), only three species were reported from this territory. Two of them, 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563DA32A3FFEA1D124" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Boissier" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[136,330,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563DA32A3FFEA1D124" box="[136,330,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563C552A3EFBDED124" authority="(Kamelin 1977: 190) Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Kamelin" baseAuthorityPageNumber="190" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[382,1077,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="badachschanica">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563C552A3EFDB9D124" box="[382,594,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. badachschanica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B56815745563F742A3FFCD3D124" author="Kamelin, R. V." box="[607,824,554,580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" pagination="187 - 192" refId="ref9868" refString="Kamelin, R. V. (1977) New taxa of Central Asian Umbelliferae. Novosti Sistematiki Vysshikh Rastenij 14: 187 - 192." type="journal article" year="1977">Kamelin 1977: 190</bibRefCitation>
) Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B5681574556397C2A3FFA4CD124" author="Degtjareva, G. V. &amp; Kljuykov, E. V. &amp; Samigullin, T. H. &amp; Valiejo-Roman, C. M. &amp; Pimenov, M. G." box="[1111,1447,554,580]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" pagination="985 - 1010" refId="ref9638" refString="Degtjareva, G. V., Kljuykov, E. V., Samigullin, T. H., Valiejo-Roman, C. M. &amp; Pimenov, M. G. (2013) ITS phylogeny of Middle Asian geophilic Umbelliferae-Apioideae genera with comments on their morphology and utility of psbA-trnH sequences. Plant Systematics and Evolution 299: 985 - 1010. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00606 - 013 - 0779 - 9" type="journal article" year="2013">
Degtjareva 
<emphasis id="B932EAB58157455639FC2A3EFAE4D124" box="[1239,1295,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">et al.</emphasis>
(2013: 1002)
</bibRefCitation>
, are common in this region and well recognizable. The third species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563EB32A5AFB92D108" box="[920,1145,590,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaerophylloides">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563EB32A5AFB92D108" box="[920,1145,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. chaerophylloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, more rarely distributed in this region, is also easily distinguished from the aforementioned species due to its remarkable fruits, separating into mericarps from the upper part.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF936A7815745563D962AAFFC01D005" blockId="13.[136,1452,446,1301]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563D962AAFFE49D1B4" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[189,418,698,724]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563D962AAFFE49D1B4" box="[189,418,698,724]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Afghan 
<collectingRegion id="4982F845815745563E2E2AAFFC65D1B4" box="[773,910,698,724]" country="Afghanistan" name="Badakhshan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Badakhshan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B56815745563E892AAFFB20D1B5" author="Rechinger, K. H. &amp; Riedl, H." box="[930,1227,698,725]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" pagination="27 - 135" refId="ref10732" refString="Rechinger, K. H. &amp; Riedl, H. (1963) Umbelliferae. In: Koeie, M. &amp; Rechinger, K. H. Symbolae afghanicae 5. Biologiske Skrifter udgivet af det Kongelige Danske Videnskabernes Selskab 13 (4): 27 - 135." type="journal article" year="1963">Rechinger &amp; Riedl 1963</bibRefCitation>
) and insufficiently studied. On the boundary territory to Tajik Gorny 
<collectingRegion id="4982F845815745563F982ACBFCD4D198" box="[691,831,734,760]" country="Afghanistan" name="Badakhshan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Badakhshan</collectingRegion>
, there are specimens morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D248157455638B82ACAFF1ED07C" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB58157455638B82ACAFF1ED07C" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These plants are very similar in their habit and possess identical leaf blades with refracted rachis, umbelles, bracts and bracteoles. The fruits of the specimens from Tajik Gorny 
<collectingRegion id="4982F845815745563E572B33FBEED020" box="[892,1029,806,832]" country="Afghanistan" name="Badakhshan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Badakhshan</collectingRegion>
separate into mericarps from the base like in the majority of species of Umbelliferae including 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563E2E2B5FFC08D004" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[773,995,842,868]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563E2E2B5FFC08D004" box="[773,995,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF936A7815745563D962B7AFA48D700" blockId="13.[136,1452,446,1301]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
We propose to treat the critical specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563FE12B7BFCDFD0E8" authorityName="Boissier" authorityYear="1844" box="[714,820,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563FE12B7BFCDFD0E8" box="[714,820,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Tajik Gorny Badakhshan as 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D248157455639EF2B7BFA4FD0E8" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[1220,1444,878,904]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB58157455639EF2B7BFA4FD0E8" box="[1220,1444,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to our molecular phylogenetic analyses, 
<specimenCount id="9D40FD2E815745563FF42B86FC63D0CC" box="[735,904,914,941]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563E9E2B86FBAFD0CC" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[949,1092,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563E9E2B86FBAFD0CC" box="[949,1092,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from this region do not group together and fall into unresolved position with 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563F9B2BA2FCA7D0B0" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Korovin" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[688,844,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563F9B2BA2FCA7D0B0" box="[688,844,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563E752BA2FBAAD0B0" box="[862,1089,950,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaerophylloides">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563E752BA2FBAAD0B0" box="[862,1089,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. chaerophylloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D248157455639542BA2FB1FD0B0" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Boissier" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[1151,1268,951,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persica">
<emphasis id="B932EAB58157455639542BA2FB1FD0B0" box="[1151,1268,951,976]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. persica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although both specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563C342BCEFE41D094" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[287,426,986,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563C342BCEFE41D094" box="[287,426,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contain slightly different ITS/ETS sequences, they are morphologically quite homogeneous. We believe the nucleotide sequence variability of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563FEF2BEAFCB8D778" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[708,851,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563FEF2BEAFCB8D778" box="[708,851,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be caused by the geographical isolation of their populations under harsh climatic conditions of Gorny Badakhshan. With this record, the distribution area of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D248157455638692C37FF1ED700" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB58157455638692C37FF1ED700" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Elwendia lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
significantly expands to the east; and the species is reported as new to 
<collectingCountry id="F351763781574556393A2C53FB94D700" box="[1041,1151,1094,1120]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
and Central Asia (
<figureCitation id="137D2A2281574556387B2C53FA7ED700" box="[1360,1429,1094,1120]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[136,229,995,1017]" captionTargetBox="[160,1423,195,956]" captionTargetId="figure-25@6.[151,1436,190,971]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. General views of mericarps. A, Elwendia darwasica. B, Elwendia schistosa. C, Elwendia varsobica. D, Elwendia kuhitangi. E, Elwendia salsa. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6479430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6479430/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35C652C815745563D962C7FFA82D674" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF936A7815745563D962C7FFA82D674" blockId="13.[136,1452,446,1301]" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">
ITS and ETS data do not allow to differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563FFD2C7EFC88D7E4" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[726,867,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563FFD2C7EFC88D7E4" box="[726,867,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563E812C7EFBAFD7E4" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Korovin" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[938,1092,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563E812C7EFBAFD7E4" box="[938,1092,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D248157455639562C7EFAB6D7E4" box="[1149,1373,1130,1156]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chaerophylloides">
<emphasis id="B932EAB58157455639562C7EFAB6D7E4" box="[1149,1373,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. chaerophylloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to unresolved relationships between different accessions of these species. In contrast, morphological characters allow easy identification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563CAD2CA6FDFED7AC" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[390,533,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563CAD2CA6FDFED7AC" box="[390,533,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563E232CA6FC48D7AC" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Korovin" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[776,931,1202,1228]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563E232CA6FC48D7AC" box="[776,931,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by solid (vs. hollow) stems, longer terminal segments of radical leaves (
<quantity id="4CBE9B42815745563C952CC3FDF7D791" box="[446,540,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
vs. 
<quantity id="4CBE9B42815745563F622CC3FD41D791" box="[585,682,1238,1265]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 mm</quantity>
), a lower number of umbel rays (2–7 vs. 10–23) and a lower number of bracteoles (2–5 vs. 6–10). These characters suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D24815745563E362CEEFC42D674" authorityName="Pimenov &amp; Kljuykov" baseAuthorityName="Rechinger &amp; Riedl" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[797,937,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Elwendia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindbergii">
<emphasis id="B932EAB5815745563E362CEEFC42D674" box="[797,937,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="268">E. lindbergii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be retained as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
